POSITION SUMMARY 
The VP, US Commercial Sales leader reports directly to the EVP and Chief Commercial Officer. This position will have direct management and leadership responsibilities for managing Divisional Managers (DMs) within their assigned Region, as well as the entire US Sales representative team. She/he will develop DMsâ€™ leadership and coaching skills to empower his/her team to succeed with individual and group goals. The VP will also have indirect management and leadership responsibilities for up to 100 Sales Representatives working within the US. This position requires a high-level of communication and leadership to provide strategic planning and direction to the Sales Force. 
 
The VP will be accountable for the sales results, including defining specific action plans to capitalize on national market opportunities. They should model and foster a positive work environment and culture that encourages the investigation and evaluation of emerging ideas to enhance organizational performance. In addition, this individual should demonstrate a thorough understanding of all Company and competitive products (i.e., package inserts, costs, product features/benefits, side effects, clinical reprints/studies) to enhance the sales process and drive sales results. She/he should translate function and organizational strategies/goals into clearly communicated team and individual goals and expectations, ensuring all personnel comprehend goals, roles, responsibilities and how their day-to-day activities impact customers/company performance. The ideal candidate will bring an accountable culture, a visionary perspective, and a proven aptitude for teaching first level leaders. 
 
 Position will be filled at level commensurate with experience. 
 
